Apex of Zimbabwe Aiming to Sell Its Unprofitable Businesses, Newsday Says

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-04-26T08:50:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/apex-of-zimbabwe-aiming-to-sell-its-unprofitable-businesses-newsday-says.html
Apex Corp. of Zimbabwe Ltd., a
diversified company, plans to sell some of its unprofitable
operations, Newsday reported, citing Chairman Farai Rwodzi.  The company, which posted a loss of $2.3 million last year,
has received a “firm offer” for its All Metal Foundry (Pvt)
Ltd. unit in the western city of Bulawayo, the Harare-based
newspaper said. Apex is also selling its Marondera Foundry and
Philpott and Collins, an office supply company, Newsday said.  Apex, based in Harare, has temporarily closed its Zimcast
(Pvt) Ltd. unit while it seeks funding for the business, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Durban at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 